{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid, weigh potatoes into it and set aside.","Place water into mixing bowl and heat <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, peel and cut reserved potatoes into pieces (3 cm).","Place Varoma into position and place potatoes into it. Season with salt, secure Varoma lid and cook <b>18-20 min\/Varoma\/speed 4<b> or until potatoes are soft. Meanwhile, finely slice spring onions\/shallots and radishes and place into a bowl. Cut cucumber into slices (5 mm) and add to bowl with radishes.","Add coriander to bowl with radishes, toss to combine and set aside. Remove Varoma and transfer potatoes into a large bowl. Rinse and dry mixing bowl.","Place mayonnaise, vinegar, oil, wasabi, lemon juice and salt into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into bowl with potatoes and gently stir to combine. Transfer into a large serving bowl  and top with reserved salad. Sprinkle with nori (optional) before serving warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1200 g potatoes","500 g lukewarm water","½ tsp salt, plus extra to season","3 spring onions\/shallots","4 red radishes","½ continental cucumber, deseeded","2 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only","150 g mayonnaise (see Tip)","40 g rice wine vinegar","1 tsp sesame oil","20 - 30 g wasabi paste, to taste","40 g lemon juice (approx. 1 lemon)","1 nori sheet, finely sliced (optional)"]}],"id":"r256220","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-YhOm3TN14XQ\/XZWYTidqeVI\/AAAAAAAAd74\/9QD12JM0E48rrYHfoIZgII_3zvqMarLqwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6bbha1tw0FghS_zQ.png","title":"Warm wasabi potato salad","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.9 g","fat":"20.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27 g","calories":"1340 kJ \/ 319.1 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, bowl, large serving bowl","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own mayonnaise, please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>. Making your own mayonnaise will increase the total time of recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","30m","6 portions"]}